Subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pooja_Sharma
Object: Pooja Sharma is an Indian television actress and model. She is most popular for her role as Draupadi in the mythological TV show 'Mahabharat'.

Subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/To_Please_a_Lady
Object: To Please a Lady is a 1950 romantic drama film produced and directed by Clarence Brown and starring Clark Gable and Barbara Stanwyck. The climactic race scene was shot at the Indianapolis Motor Speedway.

Subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amy_Bach
Object: Amy Bach is an American author, journalist, and attorney. She won the 2010 Robert F. Kennedy Book Award for Ordinary Injustice: How America Holds Court.She has served as the Haywood Burns Fellow at The Nation magazine, and was the recipient of an Echoing Green Fellowship in 2011.She is the Executive Director of Measures for Justice, a non-profit organization that collects and analyzes data about the American justice system.

Subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/Man_in_the_Moon_(film)
Object: Man in the Moon is a 1960 comedy film directed by Basil Dearden. The film stars Kenneth More and Shirley Anne Field.

Subject: http://dbpedia.org/resource/2010_Prosperita_Open
Object: The 2010 Prosperita Open was a professional tennis tournament played on red clay courts. It was part of the 2010 ATP Challenger Tour. It took place in Ostrava, Czech Republic between April 26 and May 2, 2010.
